Troubleshooting Tips
Container won't start:

Check if port 5000 is already in use: sudo lsof -i :5000
Verify Docker is running: docker ps
Health checks timing out:

Increase timeout values in config/deployment.yaml
Check container logs: docker logs <container-id>
Rollback not working:

Ensure previous container still exists: docker ps -a
Check if keep_previous is set to true in config
Permission denied errors:

Ensure scripts are executable: chmod +x deployment-scripts/*.py
Verify Docker group membership: groups
Conclusion
You have successfully implemented a production-grade deployment gate system with automatic rollback capabilities. This lab demonstrated:

Deployment Gates: Health and readiness checks that protect customer-facing systems
Automatic Rollback: Immediate restoration of previous stable version on failure
Safety Mechanisms: Multi-layer verification before accepting new deployments
These patterns are critical for retail and e-commerce systems where downtime directly impacts revenue. The deployment gate ensures that only healthy versions reach customers, while automatic rollback minimizes the blast radius of failed deployments.

Key Takeaways:

Always implement health checks before routing traffic
Automate rollback decisions to reduce MTTR (Mean Time To Recovery)
Keep previous versions available for quick restoration
Test failure scenarios regularly to validate rollback mechanisms
